Oh and every single table in the place was maddeningly sticky!  Why?  At 9am in the morning mind you.  And I find it ridiculous that you have to warm your own muffin using the **microwave** in the public area next to the condiments that is on a shelf about 6 inches off the ground. I've been to most locations within a 15 mile radius. I just went to this one for the first time today. They asked my friend for her Panera card but didn't ask me for mine, even though we ordered separately and I'd mentioned having my Panera card while she was looking for hers. After I placed my order and the receipt printed out, I realized they hadn't asked me for my card and I said "aw man, I was hoping to use my Panera card!" The cashier looked at me and deadpanned "yeah." I don't think it was anything personal to me; I'm a respectful customer and worked in food service for 5 years. The cashier got both of our orders wrong; my friend was charged for a full salad with half a soup instead of a you-pick-two, and I was charged for a whole sandwich instead of the half I ordered. I went to the front and was refunded $2 and change for my half a sandwich, which they took to the back. I got a frozen strawberry watermelon lemonade as well and I'm not sure if it was the recipe or the way this particular one was made, but it was so disappointing I threw it away (rather than ask for a refund on a second item). Lastly, I found out they don't validate parking tickets. There is 'Columbia Parking' around the corner but I'm not sure if that's free. Also please be aware there is no outdoor seating.
Love Panera, but be warned that they don't validate for garage parking! Even though it's right there in Rockville Town Center! :(
